  "local_port": 38112,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the examples of people who skipped school or were bad in studies and are succesful now?",
  "response": "There are numerous examples of individuals who struggled with traditional schooling, skipped classes, or were considered \"bad\" students but went on to achieve remarkable success in various fields. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### **Entrepreneurs and Business Leaders**\n1. **Steve Jobs**  \n   - The co-founder of Apple dropped out of Reed College after just six months. Despite his lack of formal education, he revolutionized technology and became one of the most influential entrepreneurs in history.\n\n2. **Richard Branson**  \n   - The founder of Virgin Group struggled with dyslexia and dropped out of school at 16. He went on to build a multi-billion-dollar empire spanning industries like music, airlines, and space travel.\n\n3. **Mark Zuckerberg**  \n   - The co-founder of Facebook dropped out of Harvard University to focus on building the social media platform. He is now one of the world\u2019s youngest billionaires.\n\n4. **Bill Gates**  \n   - Although he excelled academically, Gates dropped out of Harvard to co-found Microsoft. He is now one of the richest people in the world and a prominent philanthropist.\n\n---\n\n### **Artists and Entertainers**\n1. **Jay-Z**  \n   - The rapper and entrepreneur grew up in a rough neighborhood and dropped out of high school. He is now a successful musician, businessman, and billionaire.\n\n2. **Oprah Winfrey**  \n   - Oprah faced a difficult childhood and was originally expelled from school. She later became one of the most influential media moguls and philanthropists in the world.\n\n3. **Lady Gaga**  \n   - The Grammy-winning singer dropped out of NYU\u2019s Tisch School of the Arts to pursue her music career. She has since become a global icon.\n\n---\n\n### **Inventors and Innovators**\n1. **Thomas Edison**  \n   - Edison was homeschooled after being labeled \"difficult to teach\" by his teachers. He went on to become one of the most prolific inventors in history, holding over 1,000 patents.\n\n2. **Albert Einstein**  \n   - While not a dropout, Einstein struggled in school and was considered a mediocre student. He later revolutionized physics with his theories of relativity.\n\n---\n\n### **Athletes**\n1. **Michael Jordan**  \n   - The basketball legend was initially cut from his high school team but went on to become one of the greatest athletes of all time.\n\n2. **LeBron James**  \n   - LeBron dropped out of high school early to enter the NBA draft. He is now a basketball superstar and successful entrepreneur.\n\n---\n\n### **Writers and Creatives**\n1. **J.K. Rowling**  \n   - The author of the Harry Potter series faced financial struggles and was a single mother on welfare before becoming one of the best-selling authors in history.\n\n2. **Stephen King**  \n   - King struggled academically and with substance abuse early in his career but went on to become one of the most successful and prolific authors of all time.\n\n---\n\n### **Tech Innovators**\n1. **Elon Musk**  \n   - While Musk completed some formal education, he dropped out of a Stanford PhD program to pursue entrepreneurial ventures. He is now the founder of companies like Tesla, SpaceX, and Neuralink.\n\n2. **Larry Ellison**  \n   - The co-founder of Oracle dropped out of college twice before building one of the largest software companies in the world.\n\n---\n\nThese examples show that success is not always tied to traditional education or academic performance. Many of these individuals found their passion, worked hard, and pursued unconventional paths to achieve greatness.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
